        "id": 2362653,
        "name": "Dale McClaran",
        "username": "Dale_McClaran",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/dale_mcclaran/{size}/683_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-02-20T16:54:25.000Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/wine.asp?iWine=2030110\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2013 Claude Dugat Gevrey-Chambertin</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Nuits, Gevrey-Chambertin (2/20/2018)</em><br>\nDecanted 1.5 hrs but I would have preferred to give it so much more air. A bit sullen on the nose, eventually it gained a little momentum. Clearly in the dark fruit spectrum from a pure taste analytic, yet the snap and crackle of the wines acidity gave the overall feel of a zesty red fruited drink. Lots of good things lurking underneath, but simply too young to really get to know them well. The overall balance seems to be there, so I\u2019d expect a nice return on this down the road, I don\u2019t really have the experience with Red Burgs to say when. <em><strong>(90 pts.)</strong></em>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
