        "created_at": "2018-02-20T19:53:41.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Nice\u2014and accurate\u2014note.</p>\n<p>One decade-plus is the rule for the more backward vintages of Claude Dugat\u2019s Gevrey AOC. 2002 and 2001 are drinking beautifully now, for example.</p>\n<p>My estimate would be that 2013 needs another 5 years or so to reveal some of its potential.</p>\n<p>2011 is good today with a decant, and transcends the vintage\u2019s reputation.</p>",
